Chop the @British chicken breasts{3} into 2cm cubes and place in a #mixing bowl{}. Add the @shawarma spice mix{1%sachet}, a good splash of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{}. Mix well and leave to one side.

Wash your hands. Using a clean #chopping board{} and #knife{}, peel the @red onion{1} and remove both ends. Cut the red onion into quarters and separate the inner parts from the outer layers. Cut the outer layers in half to create chunks for your skewers. Finely chop the inner parts and put to the side for later.

Now to make the skewers! Feed alternate pieces of chicken and outer red onion chunks onto the @bamboo skewers{8} until all of your chicken and outer red onion chunks are used up. Set aside.

In a #pot{} bring the exact quantity of @boiling water{600%ml} to the boil (as stated above). Remove from the heat once boiling and stir in the @bulgur wheat{125%g}. Season with a good sprinkling of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Stir in a splash of @olive oil{}. Cover the pot and leave for ~{15%minutes}.

Pre-heat your #grill{} to medium-high and then prepare the rest of your ingredients. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 1cm squares. Pick the leaves from the @mint{5%sprigs}, @flat leaf parsley{5%sprigs} and @coriander{5%sprigs}, discard the stalks and roughly chop. Zest and juice the @lemon{1}.

Cook the chicken skewers under your grill for ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway through to ensure even cooking.

> The chicken is cooked when it's no longer pink in the middle.

For the dressing, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) and mix with the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}.

Whilst your chicken continues to cook, stir your chopped herbs, finely chopped onion, red pepper, lemon zest and juice into your bulgur wheat and then taste for seasoning. Stir in another splash of @olive oil{}.

Place your chicken skewers on top of a generous pile of your tabbouleh and finish with a dollop of garlicky yoghurt. Sprinkle with @pomegranate seeds{1} and serve.